data.current_description:
**This endpoint allows you to retrieve the branded link associated with a subuser.**

Link branding can be associated with subusers from the parent account. This functionality allows subusers to send mail using their parent's link branding. To associate link branding, the parent account must first create a branded link and then validate it. The parent may then associate that branded link with a subuser via the API or the [Subuser Management page of the Twilio SendGrid App](https://app.sendgrid.com/settings/subusers).
data.description_suggestion: Retrieves the branded link configuration associated with a specified subuser. Link branding allows subusers to send mail using their parent account's branded links. The parent account must first create and validate a branded link before associating it with a subuser via the API or Subuser Management page. Requires the subuser ID as a parameter. Returns the branded link object containing domain configuration and validation status. Subusers can only retrieve their own associated branded link.
data.reasoning: Description lacks clarity on required input parameters (subuser ID) and expected output structure. Added specific details about parameter requirements, return value structure, and access control for AI agents to better understand how to construct requests and interpret responses.

data.current_description:

Link branding can be associated with subusers from the parent account. This functionality allows subusers to send mail using their parent's link branding. The parent may then associate that branded link with a subuser via the API or the [Subuser Management page of the Twilio SendGrid App](https://app.sendgrid.com/settings/subusers).

Your request will receive a response with a 204 status code if the disassociation was successful.
data.description_suggestion: Removes the branded link association from a specified subuser. This operation disassociates the parent account's branded link from the subuser, preventing the subuser from using that link branding for email sends. Requires the subuser ID as a parameter. Returns a 204 No Content status code on successful disassociation. After disassociation, the subuser will revert to using default SendGrid-branded links unless another branded link is associated.

Added clarity on parameter requirements (subuser ID), explicit response code (204), and the consequence of disassociation for AI agents to properly construct requests and handle responses.

You can submit this request on behalf of a subuser by including their ID in the `on-behalf-of` header.

data.current_description:
**This endpoint allows you to retrieve the branded link associated with a subuser.**

Link branding can be associated with subusers from the parent account. This functionality allows subusers to send mail using their parent's link branding. To associate link branding, the parent account must first create a branded link and then validate it. The parent may then associate that branded link with a subuser via the API or the [Subuser Management page of the Twilio SendGrid App](https://app.sendgrid.com/settings/subusers).
data.description_suggestion: Retrieves the branded link configuration associated with a specified subuser. Link branding allows subusers to send mail using their parent account's branded links. The parent account must first create and validate a branded link before associating it with a subuser via the API or Subuser Management page. Requires the subuser ID as a parameter. Returns the branded link object containing domain configuration and validation status. Subusers can only retrieve their own associated branded link.

**This endpoint allows you to take a branded link away from a subuser.**

Link branding can be associated with subusers from the parent account. This functionality allows subusers to send mail using their parent's link branding. To associate link branding, the parent account must first create a branded link and validate it. The parent may then associate that branded link with a subuser via the API or the [Subuser Management page of the Twilio SendGrid App](https://app.sendgrid.com/settings/subusers).

Your request will receive a response with a 204 status code if the disassociation was successful.
data.description_suggestion: Removes the branded link association from a specified subuser. This operation disassociates the parent account's branded link from the subuser, preventing the subuser from using that link branding for email sends. Requires the subuser ID as a parameter. Returns a 204 No Content status code on successful disassociation. After disassociation, the subuser will revert to using default SendGrid-branded links unless another branded link is associated.
